{
  "texts": [
    "But this is more than we need for local first-order correspondence.",
    "It suffices to find a formula σ ∈ L 1 (I) with free variables including u and u 1,..., u n such that the formula ∀u 1... ∀u n ST x (φ)[σ/Q] ∈ L 1 (I) has exactly x free and is equivalent to the second-order translation ∀Q(RO(Q) → ST x (φ)) of φ.",
    "Thus, we are using σ[α/u] to pick out a family of subsets by varying parameters.",
    "This is an example of the more general method of substitutions for first-order correspondence (see van Benthem 1983, pp.",
    "108-9) that Yamamoto [2017] uses to prove that every Sahlqvist modal formula has a first-order correspondent over full possibility frames.Before leaving the minimal valuation method, let us generalize Example 6.18."
  ]
}